<div class="answercell post-layout--right">
        <div class="js-endorsements" data-for-answer="16597876">
</div>

    
    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
<p>As of PHP 5.4, you can accomplish this with <a href="http://php.net/trait" rel="noreferrer">Traits</a>. To quote the official documentation:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Traits [enable] a developer to reuse sets of methods freely in several independent classes living in different class hierarchies. [...] A Trait is similar to a class, but only intended to group functionality in a fine-grained and consistent way. It is not possible to instantiate a Trait on its own. It is an addition to traditional inheritance and enables horizontal composition of behavior; that is, the application of class members without requiring inheritance.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Using a trait allows you to store helper methods that address cross-cutting concerns in a central place and use these methods in whatever classes you need.</p>

<pre class="lang-php s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-php"><span class="hljs-comment">// File "HelperMethodTrait.php"</span>
<span class="hljs-class"><span class="hljs-keyword">trait</span> <span class="hljs-title">HelperMethodTrait</span>
</span>{
    <span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">function</span> <span class="hljs-title">myIncredibleUsefulHelperFunction</span>(<span class="hljs-params"/>)
    </span>{
        <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> <span class="hljs-number">42</span>;
    }
}

<span class="hljs-comment">// File "MyClass.php"</span>
<span class="hljs-class"><span class="hljs-keyword">class</span> <span class="hljs-title">MyClass</span>
</span>{
    <span class="hljs-keyword">use</span> <span class="hljs-title">HelperMethodTrait</span>;

    <span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">function</span> <span class="hljs-title">myDomainSpecificFunction</span>(<span class="hljs-params"/>)
    </span>{
        <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> <span class="hljs-string">"foobar"</span>;
    }
}

<span class="hljs-variable">$instance</span> = <span class="hljs-keyword">new</span> <span class="hljs-title class_">MyClass</span>();
<span class="hljs-variable">$instance</span>-&gt;<span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">myIncredibleUsefulHelperFunction</span>(); <span class="hljs-comment">// 42</span>
</code></pre>
    </div>
