<div class="answercell post-layout--right">
        <div class="js-endorsements" data-for-answer="20809379">
</div>

    
    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
<p>If your only goal is to make the class definition file smaller, you can include files within a function definition</p>
<pre class="lang-php s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-php"><span class="hljs-class"><span class="hljs-keyword">class</span> <span class="hljs-title">MyClass</span> </span>{
    <span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">function</span> <span class="hljs-title">doStuff</span>(<span class="hljs-params"><span class="hljs-variable">$foo</span>,<span class="hljs-variable">$bar</span></span>) </span>{
        <span class="hljs-keyword">global</span> <span class="hljs-variable">$quz</span>;
        <span class="hljs-keyword">include</span>(<span class="hljs-string">'MyClass.doStuff.php'</span>);
    }
}
</code></pre>
<p>Within the include, your local scope applies ($foo,$bar and $quz will be defined)</p>
<p>I'm not sure what the overhead is - the include seems to happen at run-time, not compile time (since an include can actually return a value ..)</p>
    </div>
